request.description:
### GET /api/orphans/{orphanId}/{orphanageId}

This endpoint retrieves information about a specific orphan in an orphanage.

#### Request

No request body is required for this endpoint.

- `orphanId` (path parameter) : The ID of the orphan (string)

- `orphanageId` (path parameter) : The ID of the orphanage (string)


#### Response

The response will be a JSON object with the following schema:

``` json
{
  "status": "string",
  "data": {
    "orphan": [
      {
        "_id": "string",
        "name": "string",
        "age": 0,
        "gender": "string",
        "educationStatus": "string",
        "healthCondition": "string",
        "orphanage": {
          "_id": "string",
          "name": "string",
          "location": "string"
        },
        "orphanageAdmin": {
          "_id": "string",
          "email": "string"
        },
        "sponsors": [],
        "photos": "string or null",
        "createdAt": "string",
        "__v": 0
      }
    ]
  }
}

 ```

The response contains the status of the request and the details of the orphan including their ID, name, age, gender, education status, health condition, orphanage details, orphanage admin details, sponsors, photos, and creation timestamp.

