### POST /api/deliveryRequest

This endpoint is used to create a delivery request.

#### Request

- Method: POST

- Base URL: {{BASE_URL}}

- Headers:

    - Content-Type: application/json

- Body:

    - donation (string, required): The ID of the donation.

    - orphanage (string, optional): The ID of the orphanage.

    - location (object, required): The coordinates of the pickup location.

        - coordinates (array, required): An array containing the longitude and latitude of the pickup location.

    - destination (object, required): The coordinates of the delivery destination.

        - coordinates (array, required): An array containing the longitude and latitude of the delivery destination.


#### Response

The response is in JSON format with the following schema:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "status": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "message": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "data": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "deliveryId": {
          "type": "string"
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

 ```

- status (string): The status of the response.

- message (string): A message accompanying the response.

- data (object): An object containing the delivery ID.

The API endpoint `POST /api/deliveryRequest/claim/{id}` is used to claim a delivery request with the specified ID.

### Response

The response for this request follows the JSON schema below:

